HEADWORD: Biodynamical
<hw>Bi`o*dy*nam"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos>} <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to biodynamics, or the doctrine of vital forces or
energy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>of or pertaining to a method of farming that uses
only organic fertilizers (rather than chemical fertilizers) and organic
materials for improving the soil characteristics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Biodynamics</ent>⟦br⟧
